        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 6:04PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 604 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northwest of Greenhorn Mountain, or 31 miles southwest of
Pueblo, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greenhorn Mountain, Rye, Beulah, San Isabel, Colorado City, and Oak
Ridge Burn Scar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
